@@TJvAudioFormat
Summary
  This class describes the Audio Format used in the video stream.
Description
  Read the values to know what audio format is used, set the values to choose the audio
  format you want to use. When setting values, ensure they are correct and then call Apply.
  If some values are not correct for your configuration, Apply will return false.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.Apply
Summary
  Tries to apply the values in the properties of the audio format object to the video stream
  to which this audio format is linked to.
Description
  When you make modifications to the values of the properties, you must call this function
  or your changes will be ignored when you start grabbing.
  The most common and simple audio format to use is WAVE_FORMAT_PCM as it is always available
  on all machines but it doesn't provide any compression.
Return value
  True if the values were correct and successfully applied, false otherwise.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.AvgBytesPerSec
Summary
  The average number of bytes per second in the audio stream.
Description
  This value must be calculated according to the provider of the audio format you want to use and
  that you indicated by setting the value of FormatTag.
  Please not that if FormatTag is equal to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, the value of AvgBytesPerSec will be
  ignored and will be computed according to the recommandation for this format:

  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
     AvgBytesPerSec := SamplesPerSec * ((Channels * BitsPerSample) div 8)
  <AUTOLINK ON>
  </CODE>
See Also
  FormatTag, SamplesPerSec, Channels, BitsPerSample, FillWaveFormatEx
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.BitsPerSample
Summary
  The number of bits per sample in the audio format.
Description
  If FormatTag is set to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, this value must be either 8 or 16.
See Also
  FormatTag, FillWaveFormatEx
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.BlockAlign
Summary
  Block alignment in Bytes.
Description
  This value depends on the value of FormatTag. If it is equal to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, then the
  value of BlockAlign will be ignored and computed according to.

  <AUTOLINK OFF>
  <CODE>
     BlockAlign := (Channels * BitsPerSample) div 8
  </CODE>
  <AUTOLINK ON>
See Also
  FormatTag, Channels, BitsPerSample, FillWaveFormatEx
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.Channels
Summary
  Number of channels in the audio stream.
Description
  1 for mono, 2 for stereo.
See Also
  FormatTag, FillWaveFormatEx
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.Extra
Summary
  Some extra data required by the format indicated by FormatTag.
Description
  If FormatTag is equal to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, then the value of Extra is ignored.
  Please refer to the provider of the audio format you want to use for information on
  the data to put in this buffer.
See Also
  FormatTag, FillWaveFormatEx
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.ExtraSize
Summary
  Size of the Extra buffer in bytes.
Description
  Size of the Extra buffer in bytes.
See Also
  Extra, FillWaveFormatEx
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.FillWaveFormatEx
Summary
  Fills a WAVEFORMATEX structure with the informations contained in the properties.
Description
  The WAVEFORMATEX structure will be filled with the required informations from the
  properties of the TJvAudioFormat object. If the FormatTag is WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, the values
  will be set to comply with the recommandations for this format.
  If set to another value, the properties will be copied straight into the structure without
  any check.
Parameters
  wfex - The WAVEFORMATEX structure to be filled
See Also
  FormatTag
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.FormatTag
Summary
  The tag identifying the audio format used.
Description
  This value identifies the audio format used. If set to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM it will provoke
  a different behaviour in FillWaveFormatEx.
See Also
  FillWaveFormatEx
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvAudioFormat.SamplesPerSec
Summary
  Number of samples per second in the audio stream.
Description
  If FormatTag is set to WAVE_FORMAT_PCM, then usual values for SamplesPerSec are 8000, 11025,
  22050, 44100 as they specify the frequency in Hertz at which the sampling will be done.
See Also
  FormatTag, FillWaveFormatEx
