@@TJvCaptureSettings.PercentDropForError
Summary
  The percentage of frames dropped above which the capture is aborted in error.
Description
  When capturing a video stream, the processing load may not allow to capture every frame
  sent by the video device. Those frames are then dropped. If the ratio of dropped frames
  on captured frames is above this percentage, the capture is ended in error. This means
  that if you were grabbing in a file, that file will not be complete.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.StepCapture2x
Summary
  Controls whether or not to capture at twice the size of the orignal stream.
Description
  If set to true, the resulting stream will have its width and height doubled
  at the expense of processing power.
See Also
  StepCaptureAverageFrames
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.StepCaptureAverageFrames
Summary
  Controls the number of frames to be sampled to calculate a frame when using step capture.
Description
  This is only taken into account when doing step capture. The given number of frames will be
  captured and averaged to generate the resulting frame.
See Also
  StepCapture2x
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.TimeLimit
Summary
  The time limit in seconds for the capture.
Description
  This is only taken into account if LimitEnabled is true.
See Also
  LimitEnabled
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.Update
Summary
  Updates the properties of the object according to the values from the TJvAVICapture object.
Description
  This ensures synchronization between the object and the underlying system object. You
  shouldn't have to call this method directly.
See Also
  Apply
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvCaptureSettings.Yield
Summary
  Controls whether or not the capture will block the calling thread.
Description
  If set to true, when the capture starts, a separate thread is created allowing the thread
  launching the capture to continue.
  Reentrance issues must then be considered to avoid the user to launch twice the capture,
  for instance.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriverCaps
<TITLE TJvDriverCaps type>
Summary
  The capabilities of the driver on the current system.
Description
  This is a set of the following values. One or more may be present.

  <TABLE>
  Value                  Meaning
  -----                  -------
  dcOverlay              The driver can do overlay rendering
  dcDlgVideoSource       The driver can display a dialog to choose video source
  dcDlgVideoFormat       The driver can display a dialog to choose video format
  dcDlgVideoDisplay      The driver can display a dialog to choose video display
  dcCaptureInitialized   The capture driver is initialized
  dcSuppliesPalettes     The driver supplies palettes
  </TABLE>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvDriverIndex
<TITLE TJvDriverIndex type>
Summary
  The index of the driver to use.
Description
  As the maximum number of drivers in the system is 10, this type has been created to ensure
  the value is always correct. -1 specifies that no connection is established.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvNumAudioBuffer
<TITLE TJvNumAudioBuffer type>
Summary
  The number of audio buffer to use.
Description
  As it is a system restriction to use at most 10 audio buffers, this type has been created
  to ensure the values are always correct.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPalette
Summary
  A palette to use for the capture session.
Description
  When capturing at a Bit Depth of 8 or less bits, a palette must be used to render the
  frames. This class provides the encapsulation around the palette offered by the system.
  The easiest way to use it is to let the system create a palette automatically by calling
  AutoCreate.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPalette.AutoCreate
Summary
  Automatically create the best palette.
Description
  The best possible palette will be created for a maximum number of nbColors. It will be
  computed from the first nbFrames frames in the video stream.
Parameters
  nbFrames - The number of frames to consider for the creation of the palette.
  nbColors - The maximum number of colors the palette can contain.
Return value
  True if the palette was successfully created
See Also
  ManuallyCreate, PasteFromClipboard, Load
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPalette.Load
Summary
  Loads the palette from a file.
Description
  Tries to load the palette from the given file.
Parameters
  FileName - the name of the file containing the palette to load.
Return value
  True if the palette was loaded successfully, false otherwise.
See Also
  AutoCreate, ManuallyCreate, PasteFromClipboard, Save
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPalette.ManuallyCreate
Summary
  Indicates that the current frame must be taken into account to manually create the palette.
Description
  Use this call from a frame callback and set the flag to true to indicate that the current
  frame must be considered when creating the palette. Continue calling this method with flag
  set to true as long as you need it.
  Then call it again with flag set to false, to finalize the palette and pass it to the
  capture driver that will now use it.
Parameters
  Flag     - True to continue the creation, false to stop the creation.
  nbColors - Maximum number of colors in the palette.
Return value
  True if the call was successful.
See Also
  AutoCreate, Load, PasteFromClipboard, Save
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPalette.PasteFromClipboard
Summary
  Pastes the palette from the clipboard.
Description
  Pastes the palette from the clipboard.
Return value
  True if the call was successful.
See Also
  AutoCreate, ManuallyCreate, Load, Save
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPalette.Save
Summary
  Saves the current palette in a file.
Description
  Tries to save the current palette into a file that could be loaded later with Load.
  The usual extension for such files is .pal.
Parameters
  FileName - The name of the file to create.
Return value
  True if the file was created, false otherwise.
See Also
  AutoCreate, PasteFromClipboard, ManuallyCreate, Load, Save
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPaletteNbColors
<TITLE TJvPaletteNbColors type>
Summary
  The number of colors in a palette.
Description
  This type has been created to enforce the system limitation of at most 256 colours in
  a palette.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvPercent
<TITLE TJvPercent type>
Summary
  A percentage.
Description
  This type is defined to ensure that percentages in TJvCaptureSettings are not set to
  more than 100% or less than 0%.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvUsedEvents
<TITLE TJvUsedEvents type>
Summary
  The events to trigger if they occur.
Description
  You can decide to activate some events at some times. If you don't they won't be triggered
  even if their associated handler exists. The set is made of these possible values:

  <TABLE>
  Value              Meaning
  -----              -------
  ueCapControl       the OnCapControl event will be triggered
  ueError            the OnError event will be triggered
  ueFrame            the OnFrame event will be triggered
  ueStatus           the OnStatus event will be triggered
  ueVideoStream      the OnVideoStream event will be triggered
  ueWaveStream       the OnWaveStream event will be triggered
  ueYield            the OnYield event will be triggered
  </TABLE>
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
