@@TJvVideoFormat
Summary
  This contains the description of the Video format used by the device.
Description
  The TJvAVICapture component to which the video format is related to must be connected
  for the values of this object to make sense. Use theses values to gather information
  about the video stream you are capturing.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvVideoFormat.BitDepth
Summary
  The number of bits per pixel.
Description
  Read-Only. Usually 8, 16, 24 or 32.
  This value is to be read in conjunction with PixelFormat and Compression to determine
  the format of the stream being grabbed.
See Also
  PixelFormat, Compression
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvVideoFormat.Compression
Summary
  The compression used by the frames.
Description
  Each frame may be compressed using the given compression. The value can take the
  values you can get in the biCompression member of a BITMAPINFOHEADER structure.
  At the moment of writing, these values are:

  <TABLE>
  Value         Meaning
  -----         -------
  BI_RGB        No compression
  BI_RLE8       Run Length Encoding with a BitDepth equal to 8
  BI_RLE4       Run Length Encoding with a BitDepth equal to 4
  BI_BITFIELDS  No compression with a BitDepth equal to 16 or 32
  BI_JPEG       JPEG compression (Win98/Me/2k/XP only)
  BI_PNG        PNG compression (Win98/Me/2k/XP only)
  </TABLE>
See Also
  PixelFormat, BitDepth
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvVideoFormat.Height
Summary
  The height of the frames in the video stream.
Description
  The height of the frames in the video stream.
See Also
  Width
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvVideoFormat.PixelFormat
Summary
  The pixel format used in the video stream.
Description
  This can be used when copying a frame to a TImage to ensure the two pixel formats are
  compatible. Please note however that if the video stream doesn't use RGB encoding
  (it may use YUV), this value may not be accurate.
See Also
  Compression, BitDepth
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvVideoFormat.Update
Summary
